law.text:
The prosecution/grand jury level of the system shall consist of at least the following information:
Listing of each charged offense by name and KRS number;
Level of offense charged or degree of offense charged for each offense in subsection (1) of this section;
Number of charged offenses;
If the case was disposed of by the prosecutor, the nature of such disposition and the date of such disposition;
A listing of the charges disposed of in subsection (4) of this section;
A correlation of the number of offenses charged at arrest and the number of offenses brought before the grand jury, offense by offense;
Listing of each charged offense, and the level thereof, brought before the grand jury;
Listing of the disposition of each charged offense brought before the grand jury;
Date of indictment;
Listing of each charged offense, and the level thereof, for which the offender was indicted;
Listing of the number of criminal complaints brought before the prosecutor by written complaint, the offense alleged, and the disposition thereof; and
Listing of the number of criminal complaints sought by citizens upon which no action was taken by the prosecutor, the offense alleged, and the date of disposition. All data required by this section shall be supplied to the circuit clerk by each Commonwealth's and county attorney, if it is not already in the possession of the clerk.
